In-depth Development Breakdown for PhrasePal

1. Data Extraction and Preparation
Subtitle/Text Extraction:
Parse subtitle files (.srt/.vtt) using Python libraries like pysrt or custom parsers to get timestamped text lines.
If no subtitles, run audio through a speech-to-text model like OpenAI Whisper to get accurate transcripts with timestamps.
This raw text is your base data.

Preprocessing:
Clean the text by removing noise (e.g., filler words, punctuation that confuses the models).
Normalize phrases (lowercase, lemmatize) for better matching and detection.


2. Phrase and Idiom Detection
Rule-Based & Dictionary Matching:
Start with a curated list or database of common idioms and phrasal verbs.
Use keyword matching, regex, or spaCy’s pattern matcher to flag these phrases in the text.

AI-Powered Detection (Using GPT or Similar):
For more flexible and contextual detection, send subtitle lines or chunks of text to an AI model like GPT.
Prompt it to identify idioms or phrases with explanations or highlight them.
This method handles variations and new expressions better than rigid matching.

Context Awareness:
Since idioms often depend on context, consider feeding surrounding text for better phrase identification and disambiguation.


3. Explanation Generation
Prompt Engineering:
Design prompts that instruct GPT (or similar) to:

Define the phrase clearly in learner-friendly language.

Provide example sentences (ideally from different contexts).

Optionally include origin or usage notes.

Batch Processing:
Process phrases in batches to optimize API usage and speed.

Caching:
Store explanations locally or in a database to avoid repeated API calls and speed up user experience.


4. Quiz and Flashcard Creation
Question Generation:
Use AI to generate quiz questions such as:

Multiple choice (What does this phrase mean?)

Fill-in-the-blank sentences with the idiom missing.

Matching phrases with meanings.

Adaptive Learning:
Track user performance and repeat difficult phrases more often (spaced repetition logic).


5. Frontend Interaction
Phrase Visualization:
Display phrases with their explanations and examples alongside the video’s timeline or subtitle text.
Allow users to click on phrases to get more info or hear pronunciation.

Interactive Quizzes:
Provide instant feedback, explanations on wrong answers, and progress tracking.


6. Optimization & Scaling
Performance:
Use asynchronous calls when working with AI APIs to keep UI responsive.
Optimize subtitle parsing and phrase detection pipelines for speed.

Extensibility:
Architect the system modularly so you can add new features like multilingual support or voice interaction later.

User Data & Privacy:
If you store user data, implement proper data protection and privacy measures.

